spans.content: EST3 supports centralized (banked) amplifier configurations for
Model 3-ZA20 Zoned Amplifiers at the EST3 control panel provide
a channel source(s) for banked amplifiers. The 3-ZA20 amplifiers
can select any one (at a time) of the EST3 eight audio channels
as a signal source. Examples include; page, alert and evacuation.
Special interface modules, the 3-ATPINT, or MN-ABPM panel-
zoned amplifiers and passes these signals to the 1B3-125 and
1B3-250 audio power amplifiers via an Amplifier Terminal Panel
(ATP). The 3-ATPINT can pass supervised audio signals to other
ATPlNTs within a local amplifier bank or to other remote banks of
amplifiers. The 3-ATPINT mounts on the ATP.
The ATP Audio Terminal Panel interfaces one or two audio power
amplifiers and monitors utility power, charges and supervises
standby batteries, and provides switch-over to standby. Audio ris-
ers connect at this panel. It also has an integral trouble signal and
The EST3 System monitors and controls the amplifier bank through
Signature series modules such as the SIGA-CT1 or 2 input
modules and the SIGA-CR control relay. MR-201/C or MN-204/C
relays provide DPDT contacts for switching power amplifier risers
when a system has standby amplifiers.
SIGA-CC1 (Single Channel) or CC2 (Dual Channel) output control
modules command and supervise each audio circuit or zone. The
SIGA-RM1 Riser Monitor Module provides audio riser supervision.
- broad frequency response and low distortion
- charges and supervises up 40 AH batteries
- supports connection to EST3 Zoned Amplifiers
- UL approved for use in sleeping rooms
- hierarchical operation of eight distinct digital audio channels
Uses the ZA20 amplifier as a source
